HEADWORD: Arytenoid
<hw>A*ryt"e*noid</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ shaped
like a ladle; <?/ a ladle + <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Ladle-shaped; -- applied to two small cartilages
of the larynx, and also to the glands, muscles, etc., connected with
them. The cartilages are attached to the cricoid cartilage and connected
with the vocal cords.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

